    "author_association": "CONTRIBUTOR",
    "body": "### Problem\n\nFeed `<cmd>restart<cr>` too quickly produce dangling `nvim --embed` process.\n\n* `nvim -u NONE +'nn r <cmd>restart<cr><cmd>restart<cr>'`\n* Press `r`\n* `:qa!`\n* `pgrep nvim` show there's still nvim instance alive.\n\n(I found this when mistakenly use `restart` twice in a viml function..)\n\n### Expected behavior\n\nNo dangling process?\n\n### Nvim version (nvim -v)\n\ndd9ac565d867b1388266969614530bedb7da7405\n\n### Vim (not Nvim) behaves the same?\n\nno\n\n### Operating system/version\n\nlinux\n\n### Terminal name/version\n\nkitty\n\n### $TERM environment variable\n\nxterm-kitty\n\n### Installation\n\nbuilt from source",
