            "author_association": "CONTRIBUTOR",
            "body": "I'm not able to repro this either, but I'm sort of confused how this could be possible on a unix like system if you do a normal launch of nvim. My understanding of how nvim starts (if you don't explicitly start with --embed or --headless) is that first the UI process starts, then the UI process forks into the \"server\" process.\n\nBecause of that the server process is a child of the UI process, so if the UI process dies, the OS will kill the orphaned server process. I could be missing something though.",
